description_detail.description: This artistic estate has its own beach, with about 750 feet of lakefront property, 7 unique villas and a 70 foot long infinity pool. This estate includes 7 registered buildings, which consists of an elegant main home with a 2 story stunning glass wall overlooking panoramic views of the lake; a 2 bedroom home up the hill with outdoor patio, deck, and sauna; building 3 is near the pool, with 1 bedroom and bath, living space and kitchen. Building 4 has a bedroom, bathroom and shower room, building 5 is an event house with a huge deck for concerts or ceremonies as well as an outside bath and onsen style shower. Building 6 is the an authentic Japanese tea service house with a famous Kyoto temple designed roof. Building 7 has a bathroom, bedroom and outdoor kitchen with an elegant dining pavilion with amazing views. There is also an Outdoor bath, sauna and jacuzzi facing a huge waterfall feature and the other side of this bath flaunts the lake view and a giant cherry blossom tree. The sauna house has an all copper roof with a Japanese temple design. The open air jacuzzi house has a real rock wall. White marble surrounds the infinity Swimming pool which is 7 feet deep and 70 feet long and is surrounded by Greek and European style columns and imported art from Italy. You’ll find original artwork, murals and statues throughout the property almost everywhere you look, as well as a grape arbor vineyard. Enjoy viewing the beauty that surrounds you with multiple terraces that overlook the lake. In addition to the Grapes that grow on the property, there are wonderful fruit trees. You’ll find 2 Naval orange trees, 2Parsimmon trees, 2 loquats, ume (plum) and a chestnut tree. Imagine fishing here or dropping a crab pot off the jetty and catching your own seafood for dinner! Hawks and birds soar overhead, and on a clear day you can even see Mt. Fuji!The zoning is currently residental, but being in the white zone, this allows for resort or apartment zoning. There is still room to build! This area is under the state park regulations and forest regulation, so it will keep it’s beauty for your lovely life here in Japan.This large property is conveniently located between many exciting areas in Japan. Enjoy easy train access at the Hamamatsu station where you will find the Shinkansen Express. Enjoy lakefront activities like swimming, fishing, boating, crabbing, wind surfing, sea shell collecting, or take a morning walk or bike ride around the lakefront pathway. This pathway is one of Japan's most famous cycling courses, extending over 100 kilometers (60 miles). There are plenty of restaurants to choose from and Tokyu resort for a special meal is a 20 minute walk, away or just 3 minutes away by car. There are no easements on the property, no shared roads. You’ll have access to boat deck nearby on the lake or there are multiple marinas as this is a popular boating destination.

description_detail.This building was built in the Meiji era: This building was built in the Meiji era by a wealthy merchant who moved to Hakodate from far away from Honboku and made a fortune in Hakodate. It originated from a villa. Since then, it has undergone repair work every time there was a great war or a great fire in the Showa era, but the garden is still a building with a taste that reminds us of the past. There are three tea rooms, including “Matsubaan,” named by the 15th Urasenke Iemoto, Sen Soshitsu, each with its own charm. You can enjoy seasonal flowers and trees, and you can enjoy different scenery from each room. The newly created garden received the Japanese Garden Award, and you can also see this garden from the jacuzzi and indoor bath. In one corner of the garden, there is also an authentic white-walled storehouse with two floors above ground and one floor below ground.

description_detail.description: The property is located in Western Lake (Saiko) - sometimes Saiko - one of the Fuji Five Lakes and in the town of Fujikawaguchiko in southern Yamanashi Prefecture near Mount Fuji, Japan. It is only 90 minutes’ drive from central Tokyo. Saiko was declared a World Heritage site in 2013. There are diverse ways to enjoy Saiko – as beautiful spot filled with full bloomed cherry blossoms in spring, a cool highland resort in summer, famous spot for the beautiful colored leaves in fall, and hot spring and skiing in winter. In recent years, Saiko is very popular among tourists from Asian and European countries. Many cottages close to the property are owned by foreigners, and resort villas are rented by foreign companies. Also, 15 minutes’s drive will take you to the Japanese Red Cross Medical Center, famous hotels, restaurants and a shopping mall called “Forest Mall,” and you will have no trouble with daily life. In the neighborhood, there is a resort cottage the president Abe owns, which makes the area safe. If you make a little side trip, there is spots like the Gotemba Premium Outlets and Hakone Ashinoko, which is famous for its hot spring. The property has a well, so you can enjoy river-bed water of Mt. Fuji for drinking and jacuzzi bath. The property has various possibilities and will attract foreigners.
